HEADWORD: Espionage
<hw>Es"pi*o*nage</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>espionnage</ets>, fr. <ets>espionner</ets> to spy, fr.
<ets>espion</ets> spy, OF. <ets>espie</ets>. See <er>Espy</er>.]</ety>
<def>The practice or employment of spies; the practice of watching the
words and conduct of others, to make discoveries, as spies or secret
emissaries; secret watching.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

